OL,5, A mum-of-four said she felt            
OL,6, "fat-shamed" at a pregnancy scan and   
OL,7, during follow-up appointments.         
OL,9,FAlexandra Dodds said her weight was    
OL,10,Fraised at every appointment, and       
OL,11,Fcircled with a pen so vigorously in her
OL,12,Fnotes that she wanted to lose them.    
OL,14,FA study into how risk is communicated  
OL,15,Fin pregnancy, found women with obesity 
OL,16,Ffeel "deeply stigmatised".             
OL,18,FThe Royal College of Midwives (RCM)    
OL,19,Fsaid care should be based on respect   
OL,20,Fand understanding of women's needs.    
